To style your Angular PrimeNG <p-button> elements so they visually match the FIS Data Integrity Manager UI (as shown in the second screenshot), you’ll need to make a few CSS updates. Based on the screenshots and your current code, here's a suggested CSS style block and the modifications you can make:


---

✅ Step 1: Suggested CSS (Modern FIS-style UI)

Add this to your component's .css or .scss file:

.button-group {
  display: flex;
  gap: 10px;
  margin-bottom: 10px;
}

.p-button {
  border-radius: 4px;
  font-size: 13px;
  padding: 4px 12px;
  height: 32px;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
}

.p-button .pi {
  margin-right: 5px;
}

.p-button.add-button {
  background-color: #e0f7fa;
  border: 1px solid #0097a7;
  color: #006064;
}

.p-button.delete-button {
  background-color: #ffebee;
  border: 1px solid #c62828;
  color: #b71c1c;
}

.p-button.refresh-button {
  background-color: #e8f5e9;
  border: 1px solid #2e7d32;
  color: #1b5e20;
}


---

✅ Step 2: Update Your Buttons in HTML

Update your HTML <p-button> declarations like this:

<div class="button-group">
  <p-button 
    class="add-button" 
    (click)="showDialog()" 
    icon="pi pi-plus" 
    title="Add">
  </p-button>

  <p-button 
    class="delete-button" 
    (click)="deleteSelectedRates()" 
    icon="pi pi-trash" 
    title="Delete Selected" 
    severity="danger">
  </p-button>

  <p-button 
    class="refresh-button" 
    (click)="refreshPage()" 
    icon="pi pi-refresh" 
    title="Refresh">
  </p-button>
</div>


---

✅ Optional: Match Font & Button Widths

You may want to explicitly match the font family and fixed button widths based on the FIS style.

.p-button {
  font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, Verdana, sans-serif;
  min-width: 110px;
}


---

Final Notes:

You can tweak the padding, font size, colors, and border radius further to fine-tune the appearance.

If you want tooltips instead of the title attribute, use <p-tooltip> from PrimeNG for richer behavior.


